HEADWORD: Undaunted
<hw>Un*daunt"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not daunted; not
subdued or depressed by fear.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Bold; fearless; brave; courageous;
intrepid.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*daunt"ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*daunt"ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unde</ent>⟦br⟧
